postcontent:
For sale is a Brand New Kel-Tec KSG OD Green 12 Gauge pump shotgun, it comes with the box, paperwork, gun lock. Below I have listed the factory specifications and description for you to look over. If you have any questions feel free to give us a call, shoot us a email, or stop in and check out our large selection of NEW & USED firearms!

Description: The KSG is our first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape and design are similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9lbs and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1″ overall length and an 18.5″ cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 6 rounds of 12 gage 3″ shells each, for a total capacity of 6 6 1 (7 per tube if using 2-3/4″ shells). The simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard. The lever can be positioned in the center detent in order to easily clear the chamber without feeding another round from either magazine. A cross bolt style safety blocks the sear, and the pump release lever is located in front of the trigger guard. The pump includes an under Picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, or a light or laser. The included top Picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

Description: In development for more than four years, the VP9 is Heckler & Koch’s latest handgun and the first striker fired HK since the renowned P7 series pistols were introduced in the 1980s.

Experience gained by HK engineers with the recent P30 pistol had a direct influence on the design of the VP9, but the VP9 breaks new ground with its integration of a unique striker firing system with an enhanced HK “light pull” trigger. The VP9 trigger surpasses those found on competitors. It has a short, light take-up with a solid, single action type break followed by a short positive reset.

The VP9 uses HK’s ergonomic handgun grip design that includes three changeable backstraps and six side panels— accommodating all hand sizes. Molded finger grooves in the front of the pistol’s grip also instinctively position an operator’s hand for optimal shooting. Only HK handguns have such a customized grip.

VP9 pistols have an extended Picatinny MIL-STD-1913 rail molded into its polymer frame for mounting lights and accessories. The rail has been tested and certified to handle mounted accessories up to 5.6 ounces.

The VP9’s proprietary captive flat recoil spring helps reduce the recoil forces effecting the operator and the handgun, improving shooter control during rapid firing and prolonging component service life.

title: For Sale:  Beautiful 1944 WWII Spanish M43 8mm Mauser + bayonet, ammo, etc.
location: Grey Forest (NW of SA), San Antonio, Texas
postcontent:
Offered for sale is this beautiful WWII-vintage Spanish M43 8mm Mauser, manufactured in 1944 by the Fabrica de Armas in La Caruña. This is a nearly complete original weapon, offered here almost as it was originally manufactured over 70 years ago. There are matching serial numbers on the barrel, receiver, floor plate and trigger guard. The serial number on the bolt does not match the others. The stock is cartouched and apparently original, though the excellent condition of the varnish likely indicates that it was refinished. Exterior metal retains much of the original finish, say 75% or so. The action feels smooth and tight. The bore and chamber are clean and shiny, with strong rifling and little or no muzzle erosion. The sale includes the internally-mounted cleaning rod, a modern high-quality Uncle Mike's leather sling, and a bayonet with scabbard of the correct type, though with a mismatched serial number.

Also included in the sale is a bunch of ammo, and supplies to load a bunch more. This is all as I received it when I bought somebody else's collection a few years ago, so the reloads are not my work – so of course proceed with caution, same for the military surplus ammo, though in both cases, the stuff I've fired has been fine.
